<TITLE> Section 144 imposed in Shialcoal, Sirajganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Jan 20 (bdnews24.com)  Local authorities on Wednesday imposed a Section 144 ban on public meetings at Shialcoal union of Sirajganj Sadar upazila as local units of ruling Awami League and opposition BNP had planned rallies at the same time. Sadar upazila nirbahi officer Mohammad Hossain told bdnews24.com that the Section 144 was in effect from 8am and would remain in force for 24 hours. A large number of police personnel were also deployed at and around Abdullah Al Mahmud School and College playground, the planned venue of the two rallies, he added. The local administrator said BNP Shialcoal union unit called a rally at at 3pm on Wednesday. The rally was called in protest at an Awami League central leader's filing a case against local BNP MP Romena Mahmood, accusing her of vote rigging in the last general election. Local Awami League also convened a rally at the same venue at the same time, "creating chances of deterioration of law and order", said Hossain.
